cessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aOur Energy Future is an introductory textbook for the study of energy production, alternative and renewable fuels, and ways to build a sustainable energy future. Jones and Mayfield explore the creation and history of fossil fuels, their impact on the environment, and how they have become critical to our society. The authors also outline how adopting sustainable biofuels will be key to the future of energy stability and discuss a number of renewable energy options and biofuel feedstocks that are replacements for petroleum-based products. Our society is consuming energy at an alarming rate, and the authors warn that continuing fuel-usage patterns could permanently damage the environment. This book emphasizes the importance of continued scientific, agricultural, and engineering development while it outlines the political and environmental challenges that will accompany a complete shift from fossil fuels to renewable energy and biomass. Our Energy Future is an accessible resource for undergraduate students studying biofuels and bioenergy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aBiomass energyvTextbooks. 0aBiomass energyxEnvironmental aspectsvTextbooks. 0aBiomass energyxTextbooksxEnvironmental aspects. 0aBiomass energyxTextbooks. 0aFossil fuelsxEnvironmental aspects. 0aFossil fuelsxHistoryvTextbooks. 0aFossil fuelsxTextbooksxHistory. 0aRenewable energy sourcesvTextbooks. 0aRenewable energy sourcesxTextbooks. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aMayfield, Stephen P., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTit